description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Registered Nurse - Ambulatory Care - various hours available&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity within our Ambulatory Care Unit for both experienced and newly qualified Registered Nurses. We are a busy Ambulatory Care Unit who receive referrals from community services , varied specialities and the Emergency Department which offers the opportunity to care for a wide range of medical presentations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ambulatory Care is managed under the Integrated Care Business Group alongside Acute Medicine and Frailty which can offer our staff the opportunity to develop a wide range of clinical skills which are transferrable to each area. We support and nurture our staff, within individualised training needs analysis in order to support you in your career goals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exceptionally supportive team and we provide a tailor made induction unique to your individual needs. We offer new nurses to the department up to 8 weeks supernumery which will include a two week induction programme that ensures all of your core clinical competencies are up to date. We then offer our staff the opportunity to attend internal and external courses to support their learning needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a dedicated Clinical Practice Facilitator team which offers tool box training, clinical supervision and support and also support with achieving all core and role specific training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We strive for excellence and this is an fantastic opportunity to work with a supportive friendly team. If you would like to work in a fast paced environment, with a team that is passionate about delivering high quality care then this is the job for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust is committed to safeguarding and promoting the welfare of children, young people and vulnerable adults and expects all staff and volunteers to share this commitment and promote safeguarding by implementing the Trust’s policies and procedures, acting promptly on concerns, communicating effectively and sharing information appropriately.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If successful this vacancy will require an enhanced DBS check at a cost of £43.50. This cost will be deducted from your first Trust salary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;In addition to this it will be a condition of your employment that you will join the DBS update service and pay the annual subscription fee of £13.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
